The '''2016 Bulgarian Supercup''' was meant to be the 14th [[Bulgarian Supercup]], an annual Bulgarian football match played between the winners of the previous season's [[Bulgarian A Football Group|A Football Group]] and [[Bulgarian Cup]]. The game was to be played between [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]], winners of the [[2016 Bulgarian Cup Final]], and [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]], champions of the [[2015–16 A Group]].
However, prior to the match CSKA Sofia bankrupted, followed by taking another team's professional license. As a consequence, the 2016 Bulgarian Supercup final was not held.
