{{About||the TV Festival|ABU TV Song Festival 2016}} {{refimprove|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox Song Contest | name = ABU Radio Song Festival | year = 2016 | image = | theme = | logo = | final = 26 April 2016 | presenters = | director = | exsupervisor = | winner = | vote = | host = [[China National Radio]] (CNR) | venue = [[China National Radio|China National Radio Auditorium]], [[Beijing]], [[China]] | entries = 13 songs from 10 countries | debut = {{unbulleted list|{{Abu|China|Radio}}|{{Abu|Macau|Radio}}|{{Abu|Nepal|Radio}}|{{Abu|Romania|Radio}}|{{Abu|Turkmenistan|Radio}}}} | return = | withdraw = {{unbulleted list|{{Abu|Brunei|Radio}}}} | null = | interval = | opening = <!-- Map Legend Colours --> | Green = Y | Green SA = | Purple = | Red = | Yellow = Y }}
The '''ABU Radio Song Festival 2016''' was the fourth edition of the [[ABU Radio Song Festival]]s, organised by the [[Asia-Pacific Broadcasting Union]] (ABU). Originally a [[wikt:biennial|biennial]] event, the festival organisers changed its format to an annual festival commencing from [[ABU Radio Song Festival 2014|2014]]. The festival took place on 26 April 2016 in Beijing, China. Thirteen songs from ten countries took part in the festival. The hosts {{Abucnty|China|r=Radio}}, along with {{Abucnty|Macau|r=Radio}}, {{Abucnty|Nepal|r=Radio}}, {{Abucnty|Romania|r=Radio}}, and {{Abucnty|Turkmenistan|r=Radio}} all made their début in the festival. {{Abucnty|Brunei|r=Radio}} had withdrawn from the festival stating that they had not received an invitation to participate from the broadcasting union. {{Abucnty|Indonesia|r=Radio}} failed to qualify from the pre-selection stage of the festival.
==Location== {{details|topic=the host city|Beijing}} It was announced that the 2016 ABU Radio Song Festival would take place in Beijing, China.<ref name="Radio2016">{{cite web|url=http://eurovoix-world.com/china-beijing-to-host-the-4th-abu-radio-song-festival/ |title=China: Beijing To Host The 4th ABU Radio Song Festival|publisher=eurovoix-world |accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref>
== Format == Unlike the format used in the [[Eurovision Song Contest]] there are two versions of the Song Festivals, [[ABU Radio Song Festival|ABU Radio]] and [[ABU TV Song Festival|ABU TV]] Song Festivals. The ABU Radio Song Festival took place alongside the Radio Asia 2016 event took place in April 2016.
===Host broadcaster=== [[China National Radio]] (CNR), was the host broadcaster for the festival on 26 April 2016.<ref name="Radio2016"/>
==Participating Countries== A total of fourteen countries took part in this years festival. Host country China made their début in this years festival along with Macau, Nepal, Romania and Turkmenistan. Brunei withdrew from the contest. The following entries had been selected by the ABU to participate in the final of the ABU Radio Song Festival 2016.<ref name=ABURSF16>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=ABU Radio Song Festival’16: Macau, Nepal & Romania Debut|url=http://eurovoix-world.com/abu-radio-song-festival16-macau-nepal-romania-debut/|website=Eurovoix-world.com|accessdate=20 February 2016}}</ref>
