rie]], English journalist and author (d. 1934) *[[1857]] &ndash; [[Cécile Chaminade]], French pianist and composer (d. 1944) *[[1866]] &ndash; [[Matthew Henson]], American explorer (d. 1955) *[[1874]] &ndash; [[Albert Stanley, 1st Baron Ashfield]], English businessman and politician, [[President of the Board of Trade]] (d. 1948) *[[1875]] &ndash; [[Arthur Bernardes]], Brazilian lawyer and politician, 12th [[President of Brazil]] (d. 1955) *[[1876]] &ndash; [[Varghese Payyappilly Palakkappilly]], Indian-Syrian priest, founded the [[Sisters of the Destitute]] (d. 1929) *[[1879]] &ndash; [[Bob Smith (doctor)|Bob Smith]], American physician and surgeon, co-founded [[Alcoholics Anonymous]] (d. 1950) * 1879 &ndash; [[Emiliano Zapata]], Mexican general and politician (d. 1919) *[[1880]] &ndash; [[Earle Page]], Australian lawyer, academic, and politician, 11th [[Prime Minister of Australia]] (d. 1961) *[[1881]] &ndash; [[Paul Ludwig Ewald von Kleist]], German field marshal (d. 1954) *[[1882]] &ndash; [[Ladislas Starevich]], Russian-French animator, screenwriter, and cinematographer (d. 1965) *[[1884]] &ndash; [[Sara Teasdale]], American poet and educator (d. 1933) *[[1889]] &ndash; [[Hans Egede Budtz]], Danish actor (d. 1968) * 1889 &ndash; [[Jack Ryder (cricketer)|Jack Ryder]], Australian cricketer (d. 1977) *[[1891]] &ndash; [[Adolf Busch]], German violinist and composer (d. 1952) *[[1896]] &ndash; [[Marjorie Kinnan Rawlings]], American author and academic (d. 1953) *[[1898]] &ndash; [[Marguerite Bise]], French chef (d. 1965) *[[1901]] &ndash; [[Ernest Lawrence]], American physicist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 1958) *[[1902]] &ndash; [[Paul Dirac]], English-American physicist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 1984) *[[1904]] &ndash; [[Achille Varzi]], Italian race car driver (d. 1948) *[[1905]] &ndash; [[André Jolivet]], French composer (d. 1974) *[[1907]] &ndash; [[Benny Carter]], American saxophonist,