{{Infobox football biography |name=Luis Moreno |image= |image_size=200 |caption= |birth_date={{birth date and age|1981|3|19|df=y}} |birth_place=[[Panama City]], [[Panama]] |height={{height|m=1.84}} |currentclub=[[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]] |clubnumber=3 |position=[[Right back]], [[Centre half|centre back]] |youthyears1=|youthclubs1 = |years1=2000–2001 |clubs1=[[Deportivo Petare|Deportivo Italia]] |caps1=0 |goals1=0 |years2=2001–2004 |clubs2=[[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]] |caps2= |goals2= |years3=2005–2006 |clubs3=[[Envigado Fútbol Club|Envigado]] |caps3=43 |goals3=2 |years4=2006–2007 |clubs4=[[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]] |caps4= |goals4= |years5=2007 |clubs5=[[Independiente Santa Fe|Independiente SF]] |caps5=15 |goals5=0 |years6=2007 |clubs6=[[Tiburones Rojos de Coatzacoalcos|Tiburones Rojos]] |caps6= |goals6= |years7=2008–2010 |clubs7=[[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]] |caps7=51 |goals7=5 |years8=2011 |clubs8=[[Deportivo Pereira]] |caps8=8 |goals8=0 |years9=2011– |clubs9=[[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]] |caps9= |goals9= |nationalyears1=2001–2011 |nationalteam1=[[Panama national football team|Panama]]<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/pa-moreno-intl.html Luis Moreno - International Appearances]</ref> |nationalcaps1=76 |nationalgoals1=0 |club-update=29 March 2011 |nationalteam-update=24 March 2011 }}
'''Luis Moreno''' (born 19 March 1981) is a Panamanian [[Association football|football]] defender who plays for [[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]].
He gained notoriety after violently kicking an injured [[barn owl]] that had landed on the pitch during a league match between [[Junior de Barranquilla]] and [[Deportivo Pereira]]. The barn owl died due to the kick.
==Club career== Born in [[Panama City]], "Lucho" Moreno began playing football with Venezuelan side Deportivo Italia. He was signed by first division club [[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]] in 2001. He had a brief spell with Colombian side [[Envigado Fútbol Club|Envigado]] during 2005 and 2006, before returning to Tauro.<ref>[http://portal.critica.com.pa/archivo/07282006/dep22_pix.html Luis "Lucho" Moreno retorna al Tauro F.C.] - Crítica {{es|icon}}</ref> Peruvian side [[Universitario de Deportes]] attempted to sign him in 2006,<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Peru.com|title=Un panameño a la "U"|url=http://www.peru.com/futbol/AutoNoticias/FutbolPortada/2006/08/19/DetalleNoticia78457.asp|language=Spanish|date=19 August 2006}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> but he stayed with Tauro.
In January 2007, Moreno returned to the Colombian league, joining [[Independiente Santa Fe]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Prensa.com|title=Moreno es uno de los cinco refuerzos|url=http://mensual.prensa.com/mensual/contenido/2006/12/15/hoy/deportes/830187.html|language=Spanish|date=15 December 2006}}</ref> The club terminated his contract in May 2007, after a disciplinary incident.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Prensa.com|title=Luis Moreno separado del equipo Santa Fe|url=http://mensual.prensa.com/mensual/contenido/2007/05/09/hoy/deportes/976788.html|language=Spanish|date=9 May 2007}}</ref> He returned to Tauro, but shortly after joined Mexican [[Liga de Ascenso|Primera División A]] side [[Tiburones Rojos de Coatzacoalcos|Tiburones Rojos]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Panamá America|author=Figueroa, Carlos|title=Luis Moreno y Edwin fueron presentados|url=http://www.pa-digital.com.pa/periodico/buscador/resultado.php?story_id=617201&texto=uat|language=Spanish|date=18 August 2007}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
Moreno was loaned to [[Deportivo Pereira]] in January 2011,<ref>[http://www.ligapostobon.com.co/noticia/llegan-primeros-refuerzos-para-el-pereira-05777 Llegan primeros refuerzos para el Pereira] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304050614/http://www.ligapostobon.com.co/noticia/llegan-primeros-refuerzos-para-el-pereira-05777 |date=2016-03-04 }} - Liga Postobon {{es|icon}}</ref> but returned to Tauro later that year,<ref>[http://www.panamaamerica.com.pa/content/luis-%E2%80%9Clucho%E2%80%9D-moreno-regresa-al-tauro-fc Luis “Lucho” Moreno regresa al Tauro FC] - Panamá América {{es|icon}}</ref> where he would help the club win its tenth league title in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CONCACAF.com|title=Luis 'Lucho' Moreno cree en Tauro|url=http://www.fepafut.com/noticias_detail.asp?id=3775|language=Spanish|date=13 February 2014|access-date=2014-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426234455/http://www.fepafut.com/noticias_detail.asp?id=3775|archive-date=2014-04-26|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
==International career== Moreno made his debut for [[Panama national football team|Panama]] in a June 2000 [[friendly match]] against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]] and has earned a total of 76 caps, scoring no goals.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/panama-recintlp.html Appearances for Panama National Team] - RSSSF</ref> He represented his country in 17 [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches<ref>{{FIFA player|202040}}</ref> and has been a key member of the side, participating in the 2005, 2007 and 2009 [[CONCACAF Gold Cup]] finals.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]] |author1=Courtney, Barrie |author2=Saaid, Hamdan |lastauthoramp=yes |title=CONCACAF Championship, Gold Cup 2005 - Full Details |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tables/05gc-full.html |date=30 July 2005 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024022300/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/05gc-full.html |archivedate=24 October 2008 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]] |author=Saaid, Hamdan |title=CONCACAF Championship, Gold Cup 2007 - Full Details |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tables/07gc-full.html |date=19 July 2007 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024002319/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/07gc-full.html |archivedate=24 October 2008 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]] |author=Lugo, Erik Francisco |title=CONCACAF Championship, Gold Cup 2009 - Full Details |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tables/09gc-full.html |date=12 August 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140726152032/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/09gc-full.html |archivedate=26 July 2014 |df= }}</ref>
His final international was a September 2011 friendly match against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]].
==Owl kicking incident== During a February 2011 league match between [[Junior de Barranquilla]] and [[Deportivo Pereira]], Junior's unofficial mascot owl landed on the field during play and was struck by a pass. As the owl lay stunned on the field, Moreno, from the opposing team, kicked it approximately 3 meters (~10 feet) to the touchline.<ref name=smh>{{cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/sport/football/owl-kicked-by-player-dies-from-shock-20110302-1bdnt.html |title=Owl kicked by player dies from shock |publisher=Smh.com.au |date=2011-03-02 |accessdate=2012-06-12}}</ref> Shortly after, he claimed he was prompting it to fly away<ref name=kick>"[https://www.google.com/hostednews/canadianpress/article/ALeqM5i4xVl4_p5NJgzl65Ir5RumMpG3_w?docId=6097476 Football player faces sanctions for kicking injured owl in Colombia]", The Canadian Press, February 28, 2011.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://southamerican-futbol.blogspot.com/2011/02/luis-moreno-owl-abuse.html |title=Luis Moreno Owl Abuse |publisher=Southamerican-futbol.blogspot.com |date=2011-02-27 |accessdate=2012-06-12}}</ref> but in a later interview he admitted "The kick was a product of tension on the field at the time."<ref name=smh /> The owl was treated for its injuries at a local veterinary clinic, but later died of stress related to the incident. Moreno received a two-match ban, a $560 fine from Colombian football's governing body in addition to veterinary costs for the owl's treatment and was ordered to do community service at a zoo.<ref>{{cite news|author=Reuters |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2011/apr/28/owl-killing-footballer-community-zoo |title=Owl-killing footballer ordered to do community service at a zoo &#124; Football &#124; guardian.co.uk |publisher=Guardian |date= 28 April 2011|accessdate=2012-06-12 |location=London}}</ref>
