{{Infobox recurring event | name = Nob Yoshigahara Puzzle Design Competition | logo = IDCLogo.gif ‎ | logo_size = 170px | logo_alt = Nob Yoshigahara Puzzle Design Competition | logo_caption = | status = active | genre = Puzzle Competition | frequency = annually | foundation = | founder_name = [[Jerry Slocum]], International Puzzle Collectors Association |prev = [[San Diego]], [[USA]], "IPP38" |next = IPP39 | current = | last = August 2018 | location = | location_city = | location_country = | dissolved = | leader_name = Nick Baxter | begins = 2001 | prize_money = | guest = | core_members = | parent = | divisions = | people = committee members are [[Oskar van Deventer]], Gary Foshee, Marcel Gillen, Brian Pletcher, and Naoaki Takashima | slogan = | homepage = {{URL|https://puzzleworld.org/DesignCompetition/}} | footnotes = also known as 'International Puzzle Party' (IPP) }}
{{Puzzles |Lists}}
'''Nob Yoshigahara Puzzle Design Competition''' – is an annual competition of design of [[mechanical puzzles]]. The location of the competition rotate between North America, Europe, and Japan. Puzzle design competition exists since 2001, known since 2005 as the Nob Yoshigahara Puzzle Design Competition, after renowned puzzler [[Nob Yoshigahara]].<ref>{{Citation|first = Eric |last=Grundhauser |title=Solving the Mystery of the Secret International Puzzle Party |url = https://www.atlasobscura.com/articles/solving-the-mystery-of-the-secret-international-puzzle-party | year = 2016 | publisher = [[Atlas Obscura]]}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|first = Dustin|last= Nelson |title=Puzzle Master Shows How To Solve 2017'S Puzzle Of The Year |url = https://www.thrillist.com/news/nation/puzzle-of-the-year-mr-puzzle | year = 2017 | publisher = [[Thrillist]]}}</ref>
The competition is held in conjunction with International Puzzle Parties founded by [[Jerry Slocum]] in 1978, an event dedicated to discussing, showing, and trading, mechanical puzzles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.puzzleparty.org|title=International Puzzle Party|website=www.puzzleparty.org|access-date=2018-11-16}}</ref>
== Winners 2018 == [[File:IPP award.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Award 2018 San Diego from [[Nob Yoshigahara Puzzle Design Competition]]]] [[File:IPP Burr.jpg|thumb||250px|This is the IPP Burr, designed and made by Brian Young.]]
The Puzzle of the Year (Jury Grand Prize and Puzzlers’ Award) went to Casino by Volker Latussek. The Grand Jury 1st Prize was awarded to both the 5L Box by Hajime Katsumoto and Trinity by Kyoo Wong.
Jury Honorable Mentions went to: Auzzle A2 by [[Ilya V. Osipov|Ilya Osipov]], Jigsaw Puzzle 29 by Yuu Asaka, Nosey Puzzle by Alexander E Holroyd, and TicTac’s Tactics by [[Eric Harshbarger]].<ref>{{Citation|first = |last= |title=International Puzzle Party IPP38 Nob Yoshigahara Puzzle Design Competition 2018 |url = https://themetagrobologist.co.uk/international-puzzle-party-ipp38/ | year = 2018 | publisher = themetagrobologist.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|first = |last= |title=IPP38 PUZZLE DESIGN COMPETITION (IPP)|url = https://puzzleworld.org/DesignCompetition/2018/results.htm | year = 2018 | publisher = puzzleworld}}</ref>
